De Luca was recruited by the British hard rock band UFO in 2008 when former bassist Pete Way was unable to get his U.S. work visa.
De Luca joined UFO in the studio recording their acclaimed 2015 album A Conspiracy Of Stars, also contributing songwriting.
On September 29, 2017, UFO released their 22nd studio album, the self produced The Salentino Cuts, including De Luca on bass.
